     * A systematic review and meta-analysis of recent developments in
       sustainable supply chain management
       Article
          + Oct 2018
          + Int J Logist
          + Ashish Bhanabhai Patel
          + Tushar N. Desai
       The existing literature reviews on sustainable supply chain
       management (SSCM) lack in portraying the recent developments,
       possible application areas and the importance of SSCM in the
       development of nations’ industrial economy. The main aim of this
       article is to explore the emerging aspects, present trends and
       conduct the meta-analysis by performing a systematic review of the
       available SSCM literature. The present study conducts a systematic
       review of 326 SSCM articles published across referred peer reviewed
       journals during 2001–2017 in various domains such as business and
       management, engineering, healthcare and services. During the
       analysis of the literature, various categories such as publication
       year, journals, research design type, industry sectors,
       multi-criteria decision-making techniques, enablers and barriers
       are adopted. The present study is equally beneficial for
       practitioners and researchers as it displays a better understanding
       of SSCM and its developments over different industry sectors.
