     Marco Neri
   Marco Neri

   Mount Etna is among the few volcanoes on Earth that erupt nearly
   continuously, but its activity (in terms of output rate and flank
   eruption frequency) undergoes significant fluctuations in time. Such
   fluctuations do not occur randomly, but represent various stages of
   cycles on a scale of decades and centuries. Reccurent patterns are
   particularly ev...

