   Boris Behncke

   Boris Behncke

   Mt. Etna is characterized by active spreading of its eastern and
   southern flanks. The eastern unstable area is bordered, to the north,
   by the E-W trending Pernicana Fault System (PFS), previously believed
   to be ∼9 km long. Its precise eastern termination, and thus the extent
   of the collapsing area, were not clearly defined, due to the lack of
   recen...

