   The cryptic Indo-Pacific goby Trypauchenopsis intermedia Volz 1903
   caught from the muddy estuary of Jalaur River in Iloilo, Panay Island
   is reported for the first time as a new country record for the
   Philippines. A brief description and a photograph of the only specimen
   are also presented.

