   A new species of Platymantis (Amphibia: Ranidae) from the Sierra Madre
   Mountains, Luzon Island, Philippines
   Article
   Full-text available
     * Sep 1999

     * W.C. Brown
       W.C. Brown

     Angel C. Alcala
   Angel C. Alcala



   Perry S Ong

   Perry S Ong



   Arvin Cantor Diesmos

   Arvin Cantor Diesmos

   A new species, Platymantis sierramadrensis, from the Sierra Madre
   Mountains in the provinces of Aurora and Isabela, Luzon Island,
   Philippines, is described. This species is distinguished from other
   Philippines species of Platymantis (hazelae group) by its pale color,
   smooth skin, advertisement call, and other characters given in the
   diagnosis.

