   coral reef fisheries is maintenance or enhancement of yields to areas
   adjacent to reserves by adult (post-settlement) movements from reserve
   to fished areas (the so-called 'spillover effect'). Demonstration of
   this effect has been rare. This paper reports on some circumstantial
