   Effects of marine reserves on coral fish abundances and yields of
   Philippine coral reefs
   Article
     * Jan 1988

     * Angel C. Alcala
       Angel C. Alcala

   Reviews the effects of long-term protective management on fish
   abundances at coral-reef reserves and nonreserves and on fish yields at
   nonreserves at four small islands in the central Philippines. Factors
   influencing fish yields and management problems affecting Philippine
   marine reserves are briefly discussed. The data revealed that
   protection at...

