   Serotonin-induced spawning and larval rearing of the China clam,
   Hippopus porcellanus Rosewater (Bivalvia: Tridacnidae)
   Article
     * Nov 1987

     * S.N. Alcazar
       S.N. Alcazar

     E.P. Solis
   E.P. Solis



   Angel C. Alcala

   Angel C. Alcala

   Hippopus porcellanus, the China clam, was successfully induced to spawn
   sperm and eggs using intragonadal injections of serotonin at 1 mM. More
   than 5 million eggs were released. The eggs had a mean diameter of
   116.5±3.7 μm (range, 104–116 μm). Larval development and behavior were
   generally similar to those of other tridacnid species. Zooxanthellae...

